description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Specialist Biomedical Scientist, Specialist Coagulation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6 (annex U Band 6 considered)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Specialist Coagulation Laboratory is seeking to appoint an experienced Biomedical Scientist to join the team at Leeds Teaching Hospitals Trust. We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual and would welcome applications from candidates who have demonstrable experience in Haematology together with a completed Specialist Portfolio. We would also welcome applications from candidates currently working on their Specialist Portfolio, providing they include in their application the work outstanding and support required to complete.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The laboratory provides the diagnostic service for the Leeds Comprehensive Care Haemophilia Centre, with an extensive repertoire of specialist assays available 24/7, utilising state of the art analysers and equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The lab also provides support for specialist aspects of haemostasis and thrombosis for many tertiary clinical units in LTHT, working in close liaison with clinical haematologists in the haemostasis and thrombosis team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The establishment of the North West Yorkshire Haemophilia network in 2016 (comprising haemophilia centres in Leeds, Bradford and York, and serving a population of 2.6 million) has led to an increasing regional role for the laboratory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post has a ‘call in from home’ (non-resident) out of hour’s commitment. This involves working closely with the on-call Haemostasis Consultant who will contact the Specialist Coagulation BMS to authorise any out of hours testing. The successful candidate will be expected to take part in this system. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; For further details / informal visit please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Chris Wilks&lt;br /&gt; Operational Lead&lt;br /&gt; Haemostasis &amp; Thrombosis Laboratory&lt;br /&gt; 0113 2065620&lt;br /&gt; christopher.wilks@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
